<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-07T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-07T08:00:00-05:00" n="842" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d842">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/5–754: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Saigon</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MR2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">McClintock</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1"><hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi></gloss></seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Saigon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-07T21:00:00+08:00">May 7, 1954—9
                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2274. Sent Paris <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 783, Geneva <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 64, Tokyo <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 94, Manila <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 239,
                        Singapore <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 76, Bangkok <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 159, Hong Kong <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 67, London <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 48. <persName corresp="#p_DM1">DeJean</persName> informed
                        me at 2030 hours local time that central redoubt of Dien Bien Phu has
                        fallen. There is no capitulation and fighting continues on basis of
                        individual action. “Isabelle” continues to hold out. <persName corresp="#p_DCCC1">DeCastries</persName> as of 1630 when he made his
                        last report was still alive and fighting.</p>
                    <p><persName corresp="#p_DM1">DeJean</persName> said Press would not be informed
                        until tomorrow morning. I asked if he or <persName corresp="#p_NGH1">Navarre</persName> contemplated issuing an order of the day. He said it
                        was under study.</p>
                    <p>I requested <persName corresp="#p_DM1">DeJean</persName> officially to inform
                        Commander-in-Chief that I saluted the gallantry of <persName corresp="#p_DCCC1">DeCastries</persName> and his men at Dien Bien
                        Phu.</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_MR2"><hi rend="smallcaps">McClintock</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>